<item>
	<title>Bryan McLellan: Script hacks: waiting for the internet</title>
	<guid>http://blog.loftninjas.org/?p=571</guid>
	<link>http://blog.loftninjas.org/2010/11/30/script-hacks-waiting-for-the-internet/</link>
	<description>&lt;img src="http://planet.seattlewireless.net/heads/btm.jpg" align="right" alt=""&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now and then the VMs (kvm, libvirt + vmbuilder) I was cranking out would start up too fast, and the &amp;#8220;first boot&amp;#8221; script would run before the host got an IP address and had internet access. Since the first thing I was doing was downloading the Rubygems source using wget (to install chef), and since wget lacks a &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=202956#c6&quot;&gt;retry for dns failure&lt;/a&gt;, I hacked up this script to wait for the internet a bit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;brush: plain;&quot;&gt;
#!/bin/bash

# Wait for internet to come up (DHCP)
MAXWAIT=60
WAITTIME=0
host production.cf.rubygems.org &amp;gt; /dev/null

while [ $? == 1 ] &amp;amp;&amp;amp; [ $WAITTIME -le $MAXWAIT ] ; do
  WAITTIME=$(($WAITTIME + 10))
  sleep 10
  echo -n .
  host production.cf.rubygems.org &amp;gt; /dev/null
done
&lt;/pre&gt;</description>
	<pubDate>Wed, 01 Dec 2010 03:52:32 +0000</pubDate>
</item>
